column1: # Name: Malnutrition prevalence, weight for height, wasting, female

# Definition: Wasting prevalence is the proportion of children under five whose weight for height is more than two standard deviations below the median for the international reference population ages 0-59.
# Source: Compiled by World Bank; Data from WHO, Global Database on Child Growth and Malnutrition
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
